                   "message":  "GATE-STEP0-CLEAN-SET: widen step-0 poison auto-clean 8-\u003e10 (add arch-lints + editor)\n\nDispatch-tooling fix. The gate\u0027s step-0 worktree-cache hygiene cleaned 8\nCARGO_MANIFEST_DIR-embedding crates but MISSED rge-tool-architecture-lints +\nrge-editor, which the comment had \"intentionally excluded ... to keep the\nper-dispatch refresh cheap.\" That exclusion let PR #288 falsely fail:\nrge-tool-architecture-lints\u0027s forbidden_dep::tests::current_workspace_passes_all_rules\nwalks up from CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR to the workspace root, so a poisoned binary\npanics \"expected workspace root Cargo.toml at \u003cdead path\u003e\" (recurred on #289).\nThe robust rule is \"clean EVERY embedding crate\" - no per-crate exceptions (a\nper-crate \"is this one harmful?\" judgement is what let #288 through).\n\n- .ai/dispatch.verify.ps1: $bakingPkgs 8 -\u003e 10 (+ rge-tool-architecture-lints,\n  rge-editor); regen-glob comment widened to \"crates/** tools/** editor/**\n  runtime/**\"; rationale updated (arch-lints = proven gate-breaker via\n  workspace-root discovery; rge-editor\u0027s CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR uses are all inside\n  its #[cfg(test)] mod tests in main.rs - golden-project + io-gltf fixture path\n  reads that step-4 `cargo test --workspace --all-targets` compiles and runs, so\n  it is a real fixture-class poisoning vector, NOT launch logic); the step-0\n  summary line \"fixture crate(s)\" -\u003e \"path-embedding crate(s)\".\n\nVerified embedding set: git grep -l CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR over crates/tools/editor/\nruntime = 19 files in exactly 10 crates (the 8 + arch-lints + editor; no 11th).\nQueue runner Invoke-AiDispatchQueue.ps1 unchanged (only prunes worktrees; no\nmirrored clean list). Memory note rge_shared_target_worktree_cache records the\n8-\u003e10 finding (consistent).\n\nTooling only; no engine source; 0 Cargo.toml.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints (step-0 reports \"refreshed 10\npath-embedding crate(s)\").\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
